One of the biggest things when your'e applying make up is making sure your make up is well blended and seamless. I was watching TV earlier on this month, specifically Real Talk with Anele and couldn't help but notice the harsh contour line on her cheeks and suddenly wondered if people know these tricks of how to make your make up smooth and seamless. Firstly it is very important to make sure you have the right tools when you are applying your make up because if you do not you are not going to get the perfect end look that you might be going for. One of the most important things that we often overlook is making sure your make up brushes are clean. Use setting spray and setting powder to also make sure your make up stays intacts. Here is a video from Beauty YouTuber Kaiser Coby to help you see HOW YOU CAN ACHIEVE THE LOOK.  